OL,3,CSeaham celebrates much-loved WWI Tommy
OL,4,Cstatue's tenth anniversary
OL,6,FIt depicts a First World War soldier
OL,7,Fsitting on an ammunition box, with
OL,8,Fdowncast eyes, holding the barrel of
OL,9,Fhis grounded rifle in his right hand.
OL,11,FIt was displayed temporarily in Seaham
OL,12,Fto mark the centenary of the outbreak
OL,13,Fof the First World War in May 2014,
OL,14,Fbut became a permanent fixture after a
OL,15,Fcommittee of local residents raised
OL,16,F#102,000 to buy it.
OL,18,FRay Lonsdale, the sculptor of 'Tommy',
OL,19,Fsaid: "What made this really special
OL,20,Fis I wasn't funded by a council or a
OL,21,Fperson.
