OL,3,CSeaham celebrates much-loved WWI Tommy
OL,4,Cstatue's tenth anniversary
OL,6,F"The money was raised by a lot of
OL,7,Fpeople round here. There was children
OL,8,Fputting pocket money in, there was
OL,9,Fbusinesses putting a few hundred
OL,10,Fpounds in and they got to the total
OL,11,Fvery quickly.
OL,13,F"It meant that it was a people's
OL,14,Fsculptor, rather than something that's
OL,15,Fbeen hoisted upon them. It was a real
OL,16,Fsurprise to us."
