OL,3,CSeaham celebrates much-loved WWI Tommy
OL,4,Cstatue's tenth anniversary
OL,6,FOfficially named 1101 in reference to
OL,7,Fthe first minute of peace as armistice
OL,8,Fcame into force at 11am on 11 November
OL,9,F1918. However, it is more popularly
OL,10,Fknown as Tommy, the name often given
OL,11,Fto depictions of First World War
OL,12,Fsoldiers, referring to the archetype
OL,13,Fprivate soldier Tommy Atkins.
OL,15,FThe statue was relocated onto a paved
OL,16,Fplatform in 2015, under which was
OL,17,Fburied a time capsule containing
OL,18,Fdonated items, including a letter from
OL,19,FRay Lonsdale, a T-shirt, children's
OL,20,Fartworks, war remembrances, and a
OL,21,FVictory Medal.
